attributes.Long form description: The student grabs the GoPro from the table, inspects it, but does not know where the battery door is located. The student finds the battery door but struggles to open it. The student opens the battery door, removes the old battery and places it on the table. The student grabs the new battery, inserts it into the battery slot of the GoPro and closes the battery door. The student inspects the GoPro looking for the Sd card slot and the instructor tells the student it is located inside the battery slot. The student opens the battery door, pushes on the Sd card, removes it from the GoPro and places it on the table. The student grabs the new Sd card, inserts it on the corresponding slot and closes the battery door of the GoPro. The student inspects the GoPro, locates the on/off button and presses on it. The student presses the on/off button again and holds it until the GoPro turns off. The student grabs the strap from the table, inspects it but does not know how to attach the GoPro to it. The student inspects the GoPro and opens its mount. The student grabs and removes the lock screw from the strap. The student tries to attach the GoPro to the strap but struggles. The student attaches the GoPro to the straps, adjusts both of them and inserts the lock screw. The student screws the GoPro and strap together. The student removes the lock screw from the strap, detaches the GoPro from the strap and places the strap and its lock screw on the table. The student tries to attach the GoPro to the handheld grip but needs to remove the lock screw first. The student places the GoPro on the table and removes the lock screw from the handheld grip. The student grabs the GoPro and tries to attach it to the handheld grip but struggles. The student adjusts the mount of the GoPro and attaches the GoPro to the handheld grip. The student grabs the lock screw and inserts it in the handheld grip. The student screws the GoPro and handheld grip but fails. The student removes the lock screw and adjusts the GoPro on the handheld grip. The student inserts the lock screw correctly and screws the GoPro and handheld grip together. The student pulls the GoPro up on the handheld grip and rotates it. The student removes the lock screw, places it on the table and detaches the GoPro from the handheld grip. The student places the handheld grip on the table and grabs the tripod. The student removes the lock screw from the tripod, places it on the table and grabs the GoPro. The student attaches the GoPro to the tripod, grabs the lock screw, inserts it and screws the GoPro and tripod together. The student removes the lock screw, detaches the GoPro from the tripod and places the GoPro, the tripod and its lock screw on the table.
